stlib.datatypes.moving

Class MovingObject<T1 extends UnitObjectIF<T2>,T2 extends GeneralTypeIF>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stlib.datatypes.GeneralType
      • stlib.datatypes.moving.MovingObject<T1,T2>
  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - - specifies the type of the 'UnitObject' in this 'MovingObject'
    T2 - - specifies the base type of the 'UnitObject' and the 'MovingObject'

    both types have to be compatible
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    GeneralTypeIF, MovingObjectIF<T1,T2>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MovingBool, MovingPoint, MovingRegion

    public abstract class MovingObject<T1 extends UnitObjectIF<T2>,T2 extends GeneralTypeIF>
extends GeneralType
implements MovingObjectIF<T1,T2>
    Abstract Superclass for all 'MovingObject' subclasses
    Realizes the mapping of the unit objects to a single object, which represents the real moving object.
    Author:
    Markus Fuessel

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public boolean add(T1 newUnit)
        Description copied from interface: MovingObjectIF
        Add/append a new unit to this 'MovingObject' object.
        Only appending is possible, if:
        - the period of the passed unit is right adjacent with the period of the last unit, or
        - the period of the passed unit is greater as the period of the last unit

        If the value of the last unit of this 'MovingObject' is equal to the value of the passed unit and if their periods are adjacent or intersects right, then the period of the last unit will be extended
        Specified by:
        add in interface MovingObjectIF<T1 extends UnitObjectIF<T2>,T2 extends GeneralTypeIF>
        Parameters:
        newUnit - - the unit to add/append
        Returns:
        true if the passed unit was added, false otherwise
